div.p: Process lifecycle transitions in the scheduler
PCB slot available No process occupying
Invariant: In run queue Waiting for CPU time All resources allocated
Invariant: current_process Actively executing Not in run queue
Invariant: wake_time set Waiting for I/O/event Not in run queue
Invariant: exit_code set Terminated, awaiting parent wait()

div.h2: Valid - Normal state transitions ILLEGAL - Invalid transitions (shown with dashed line)

div.p: System startup Idle process created
Trigger: Create new process Guard: Free PCB slot exists Action: Allocate PCB, stack
Trigger: Context switch Guard: Process at queue head Action: Remove from queue
Cannot skip RUNNING Must be scheduled first
Trigger: Timer tick Guard: Time slice = 0 Action: Add to queue tail
Trigger: Yield syscall Guard: None Action: Voluntary switch
Trigger: Blocking syscall Guard: Resource unavailable Action: Set wake_time
Trigger: Exit syscall Guard: None Action: Store exit_code
Trigger: Unhandled fault Guard: No handler Action: Kill process
Trigger: I/O complete Guard: wake_time reached Action: Add to queue
Trigger: Timer tick Guard: ticks >= wake_time Action: Wake process
Cannot exit while blocked Must wake first
Trigger: wait() syscall Guard: Parent reaps child Action: Free PCB slot
Process terminated Memory reclaimed
Trigger: Timer tick Guard: Time slice > 0 Action: Decrement counter
